A kingdom is in rebellion against the incompetent king who is believed dead but is just in hiding. The film has 3-4 factions fighting against each other, mostly using magic and the power of chi. Not a martial arts film. Most of the film is taken up by talking about philosophy, rebellion, and forgiveness. They needed to cut out the half hour that put me to sleep. I have no idea why this has an "R" rating. Killing consists mostly of people just laying down.

I watched the film well dubbed in English with matching English subtitles.
LIKED THE 1ST 2 , AND THE 3RD DIDN'T DISAPPOINT. COMPLETED THE TRILOGY , BUT LEFT ROOM FOR MORE. GREAT SCI-FI, KUNG-FU, CRIME DRAMA, ACTION THRILLER.

I watched this movie on youtube several times. Its originally the third movie in "The Four" series. It was released in Hong Kong in 2014.  It's a little bit of a B-movie but still good. I like that Yifei Liu is in it. All of "The Four" movies are good but this one is my favorite.

Why is it that the solemn English narrator for these wuxia dramas always sound the same and says the same thing, "it was a time of..........blah,blah,blah....".  It was identical for Hero, Curse of Golden Flower, The Banquet and countless others.
I guess I've watched this out of order, looking at some of the other reviews, but I really enjoyed the movie as a stand alone even if I did miss some significance from watching this one first.

Watched on a purchased DVD. Dubbed in English and done well. Not enough action as I became bored in the middle of the film. Not as good as the first film. I found that one excellent. I have not seen Lawless Kingdom yet.

It was a typical plot and fun magical martial arts film. It was a good mix of drama and action that some people enjoy. The same kind of people that don't realise that you're reading the subtitles in the first 5 minutes. Needless to say. I enjoyed it.

I really enjoyed the movie.  It was a bit difficult to follow at first, trying to keep track of all the players, but it became clearer as the movie progressed.  The story was enjoyable and the acting very good.  Great special effects, and the ending, well, you'll just have to wait and see for yourself.
